    "rule":  "Genitiv (WESSEN?): des (+s/es), der, des (+s/es), der.",
    "explanation":  "The Genitive case shows possession or belonging. Masculine and neuter nouns usually add -s or -es to the ending. It is common after prepositions like \u0027wegen\u0027 or \u0027während\u0027.",
